:ruby
  @page_title = 'Lists'
  @nav        = :ui
  @subnav     = :lists

= box 'Basic Lists' do
  %p Basic list styling is very simple: ULs are bulleted, OLs are numbered, and list items are spaced out the same as paragraph text.

  %h4 UL

  = haml_example do
    :plain
      %ul
        %li I am a list item in a UL
        %li I am a list item in a UL
        %li I am a list item in a UL

  %h4 OL

  = haml_example do
    :plain
      %ol
        %li I am a list item in a OL
        %li I am a list item in a OL
        %li I am a list item in a OL

= box 'Unstyled Lists' do
  %p
    When you need to create custom lists, you can remove the default list styling
    with the +plain-list mixin, and then add your own styling on top.

  %p If you just want a fully un-styled list, you can also just use .plain

  = haml_example do
    :plain
      %ul.plain
        %li I am a list item in an unstyled UL
        %li I am a list item in an unstyled UL
        %li I am a list item in an unstyled UL
